@startuml seq-05-refresh-rotation
' ============================================================
' SEQ-05: POST /auth/refresh — rotation + replay-chain revocation
' Scope : Contract 05B §5B.3 refresh flow.
' Key  : On success, issue NEW refresh, mark OLD.replaced_by = NEW.
'        On replay (old presented after rotation), revoke the
'        whole chain for that user as a precaution.
' ============================================================

title SEQ-05: POST /auth/refresh — token rotation + replay detection

autonumber

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #2E7D32
  LifeLineBorderColor #1B5E20
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
  ParticipantBorderColor #1B5E20
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFEFCD
  ActorBorderColor #AA6622
  NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  NoteBorderColor #AA8800
}

actor "Dashboard" as Dashboard
participant "AuthEndpoints\n.MapPost(/auth/refresh)\n[AllowAnonymous]" as AE
participant "AuthService" as Auth
participant "IRefreshTokenRepository" as RT
participant "IJwtService" as JWT
participant "IClock" as Clock
participant "AuditService" as Audit
database  "controlit_refresh_tokens" as RTDB
database  "controlit_audit_log" as ADB

== 1. Request — refresh cookie is sent automatically ==

Dashboard -> AE: POST /auth/refresh\nCookie: refresh_token=<raw>
activate AE

AE -> AE: read raw from cookie\n(no body, httpOnly is source of truth)
AE -> Auth: RefreshAsync(raw, HttpContext)
activate Auth

Auth -> Auth: hash = SHA256(raw)
Auth -> RT: GetByHashAsync(hash)
RT -> RTDB: SELECT * WHERE token_hash=@h
RTDB --> RT: row | null
RT --> Auth

== 2. Reject: unknown / expired / already revoked ==

alt row is null
  Auth -> Audit: Record(AUTH_REFRESH_FAILURE, ip, ua, reason="unknown")
  Audit -> ADB: INSERT
  Auth --> AE: UnauthorizedException
  AE --> Dashboard: 401 Unauthorized\nSet-Cookie: refresh_token=; Max-Age=0
end

alt row.ExpiresAt < now
  Auth -> Audit: Record(AUTH_REFRESH_FAILURE, reason="expired")
  Auth --> AE: UnauthorizedException
  AE --> Dashboard: 401
end

alt row.RevokedAt != null
  note right of Auth
    REPLAY DETECTED.
    The presented token was already used and rotated.
    Either the caller replayed an old token (attacker
    with a leaked cookie), or the real user's cookie
    was stolen and used. In both cases we cannot tell
    the two apart — revoke the entire chain for this user.
  end note
  Auth -> RT: RevokeAllForUserAsync(row.UserId)
  RT -> RTDB: UPDATE controlit_refresh_tokens\n  SET revoked_at = now\n  WHERE user_id = @uid AND revoked_at IS NULL
  Auth -> Audit: Record(AUTH_REFRESH_REPLAY, user_id, ip, ua)
  Audit -> ADB: INSERT
  Auth --> AE: UnauthorizedException("Session invalidated — please re-login")
  AE --> Dashboard: 401 + clear cookie
end

== 3. Happy path — rotate ==

Auth -> Clock: UtcNow
Auth -> Auth: newRaw = RNG(32).ToBase64Url()
Auth -> Auth: newHash = SHA256(newRaw)
Auth -> RT: InsertAsync(RefreshToken{\n  user_id=row.UserId,\n  token_hash=newHash,\n  expires_at=now+7d,\n  user_agent, ip })
RT -> RTDB: INSERT
RTDB --> RT: new_id
RT --> Auth

Auth -> RT: RevokeAsync(id=row.Id,\n  replaced_by=new_id)
RT -> RTDB: UPDATE SET revoked_at=now,\n               replaced_by=@new_id\n               WHERE id=@old_id
RTDB --> RT
RT --> Auth

note right of Auth
  Chain pointer lets us walk a rotation history
  backwards for forensics without relying on timestamps.
end note

Auth -> JWT: IssueAccessToken(user)
JWT --> Auth: new_access_token

Auth -> Audit: Record(AUTH_REFRESH, user_id, ip, ua)
Audit -> ADB: INSERT

Auth --> AE: LoginResponse{ access_token=new_access_token,\n                expires_in=900,\n                user=... }
deactivate Auth

AE -> AE: Set-Cookie: refresh_token=<newRaw>\n  HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Strict;\n  Path=/auth; Max-Age=604800
AE --> Dashboard: 200 OK\n(new access token in body, new refresh cookie)
deactivate AE

note right of AE
  The new refresh cookie REPLACES the old one client-side
  because the cookie name is the same and httpOnly means
  only the server can rewrite it. The client sees only
  "my session is still alive"; it never knows the rotation
  happened.
end note

@enduml
